WEBVTT

00:06.200 --> 00:08.566
( theme music playing )

01:51.410 --> 01:54.106
( birds twittering )

02:08.820 --> 02:11.527
( man speaking on TV)

02:11.630 --> 02:14.326
Once again no rain,
but mostly high clouds.

02:14.430 --> 02:16.921
Since you got
so much information,
can you tell us

02:17.030 --> 02:18.895
why it smells like skunk
outside the studio

02:19.000 --> 02:20.638
- in Hollywood here?
- It does?

02:20.740 --> 02:23.732
Woman:
Sam, do you know
why that is?

02:23.840 --> 02:26.934
(clanks)

02:27.040 --> 02:29.577
( kettle hissing )

02:33.320 --> 02:36.687
( thumps )

02:36.790 --> 02:40.658
( kettle whistling )

02:55.700 --> 02:57.565
( water running )

03:02.810 --> 03:05.347
- ( faucet squeaks )
- ( water stops )

03:28.070 --> 03:30.300
Brenda:
OKAY. OKAY, NOW!

03:30.410 --> 03:32.298
HAPPY BIRTH DAY!

03:32.410 --> 03:34.628
WELL, THANK YOU.

03:34.740 --> 03:36.605
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

03:36.710 --> 03:39.816
- HAPPY BIRTHDAY.
- THANK YOU.

03:42.250 --> 03:45.879
- ARE YOU EXCITED TO SEE
ALL YOUR FRIEYNEEAT-IAT DAYCARE?

03:47.760 --> 03:51.025
DID YOU NOTICE ANYTHING
IN THE BATHROOM?

03:51.130 --> 03:52.529
ASIDE FROM A FEW
NEW WRINKLES, NO.

03:52.630 --> 03:55.349
IT WAS RIGHT
BY THE TOILET.

03:56.330 --> 03:57.968
ARE YOU PREGNANT?

03:58.070 --> 04:00.868
YES.

04:00.970 --> 04:03.165
THAT'S GREAT!
CONGRATULATIONS!

04:03.270 --> 04:05.465
CONGRATULATIONS?
TO WHOM?

04:05.570 --> 04:08.300
- COME ON, WHAT AM I
SUPPOSED TO SAY?
- NOTHING.

04:08.410 --> 04:11.470
- TO YOU, TO ALL OF US!
- NO NO, WHATEVER COMES UP
IN YOUR HEAD.

04:11.580 --> 04:13.616
- BRENDA, WHAT'S THE MATTER?
- NO, NOTHING.

04:13.720 --> 04:15.369
THANK YOU FOR YOUR
HEARTY CONGRATULATIONS.

04:15.480 --> 04:17.687
- COME ON, HONEY.
- ARE YOU SURE
IT'S POSITIVE?

04:17.790 --> 04:20.054
THERE YOU GO, HONEY BUN.
MAYA'S GONNA BE LATE.

04:20.160 --> 04:23.049
BRENDA, I'M HAPPY, I--

04:23.160 --> 04:25.185
COME ON, GRAB HOLD.
COME ON, BABY.

04:25.290 --> 04:27.952
- BRENDA--
- SEE YOU TONIGHT,
I GO'I'I'A GET READY FOR WORK.

04:28.060 --> 04:30.392
I'M HAPPY,
JUST TELL ME AGAIN.

04:38.870 --> 04:41.270
Billy: FUCK!

04:41.380 --> 04:43.371
HAVE YOU SEEN MY
SKI IRAQ SHIRT ANYWHERE?

04:43.480 --> 04:45.869
- YOU HAD THAT ON LAST NIGHT.
- YEAH, I DIDN'T ASK

04:45.980 --> 04:48.210
WHETHER I HAD IT ON
LAST NIGHT, I ASKED
WHETHER YOU'VE SEEN IT.

04:48.320 --> 04:50.140
I HAVEN'T.

04:50.250 --> 04:51.842
( yells )
SHIT!

04:51.950 --> 04:54.089
WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM?!

04:54.190 --> 04:56.488
( exhales )
NOTHING,

04:56.590 --> 04:59.024
I JUST DON'T THINK
I CAN WEAR CLOTHES TODAY.

05:00.200 --> 05:02.122
DON'T YOU HAVE CLASS?

05:02.230 --> 05:05.597
YEAH, WELL,
NOTHING FEELS RIGHT.

05:05.700 --> 05:08.635
LOOK, MAYBE YOU SHOULD LIKE
SEE A DOCTOR OR SOMETHING.

05:08.740 --> 05:10.105
FOR WHAT?

05:10.210 --> 05:11.939
I DON'T KNOW,
DRY SKIN?

05:12.040 --> 05:14.679
- ARE YOU FUCKING SERIOUS?
- WELL, YEAH,

05:14.780 --> 05:17.840
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW,
EVERY DAY WITH YOU
IT'S LIKE A BIGGER PROBLEM.

05:17.950 --> 05:21.113
NOT EVERYTHING IS SOMETHING
THAT YOU CAN MEDICATE, CLAIRE!

05:21.220 --> 05:23.415
I KNOW THAT.

05:23.520 --> 05:25.340
IT'S JUST
MY CLOTHES ARE...

05:25.450 --> 05:28.385
ALL HEAW TODAY...

05:28.490 --> 05:30.424
OR SOMETHING.
I WANT MY SKI IRAQ SHIRT.

05:33.400 --> 05:35.994
OKAY, I'LL HELP YOU
FIND IT.

05:36.100 --> 05:38.318
OKAY, THAN KS.

05:39.640 --> 05:42.905
( exhales )
THAT'S ALL I WANTED
WAS SOME HELP.

05:43.010 --> 05:45.433
OKAY.

05:48.910 --> 05:50.639
OKAY.

05:50.750 --> 05:53.969
SHIT, I FEEL LIKE
I STILL HAVE SOMETHING ON.
( chuckles )

05:55.850 --> 05:58.944
MARY, KEITH AND DAVID
HAVE SOMETHING THEY WANT
TO ASK YOU.

05:59.050 --> 06:01.359
I'M ON PINS
AND NEEDLES.

06:01.460 --> 06:04.054
WE'VE DECIDED
THAT WE WANT YOU
TO BE OUR EGG DONOR

06:04.160 --> 06:05.684
AND OUR SURROGATE.

06:05.790 --> 06:08.918
- BOTH?
- IS THAT OKAY?

06:09.030 --> 06:12.158
YEAH, IT'S JUST I'VE
NEVER BEEN PROPOSED TO
LIKE THIS.

06:12.270 --> 06:13.965
MOST PEOPLE ARE
SO BUSINESSLIKE.

06:14.070 --> 06:15.833
YOU GUYS ARE
SO SWEET.

06:15.940 --> 06:18.659
- WHOSE SEED
WILL IT BE?
- HIS.

06:20.110 --> 06:22.977
SO THIS IS SOMETHING
THAT YOU WOULD WANT TO DO

06:23.080 --> 06:25.469
- FOR KEITH AND DAVID?
- YEAH, I'D LOVE IT.

06:25.580 --> 06:28.344
- I DIDN'T SAY YES?
- UH, NO.

06:28.450 --> 06:30.941
OH, THEN YES YES,
OF COURSE, YES!

06:31.050 --> 06:33.211
WELL, GOOD.

06:33.320 --> 06:35.254
CAN I ASK A QUESTION?

06:35.360 --> 06:37.248
PLEASE, DAVID.

06:37.360 --> 06:40.227
WE'RE IN THIS TOGETHER.
ASK ASK ASK.

06:40.330 --> 06:42.491
IS THERE CAFFEINE IN THAT?

06:42.600 --> 06:45.467
OH, WE'RE INTO THAT
ALREADY.

06:45.570 --> 06:47.595
OKAY. IT WAS SO NICE
FOR A MINUTE THERE.

06:47.700 --> 06:50.362
NO, I WAS JUST THINKING--
I'VE READ SOME BOOKS

06:50.470 --> 06:53.268
THAT SAY CAFFEINE MAKES IT
HARDER TO CONCEIVE...

06:53.380 --> 06:55.575
SOMETIMES, THAT'S ALL.
JUST CURIOUS.

06:55.680 --> 06:57.648
MAYBE YOU'VE READ
SOMETHING DIFFERENT.

06:57.750 --> 07:00.639
I GET PREGNANT SUPER-EASILY,
DAVID, TRUST ME.

07:00.750 --> 07:02.718
IT'S KIND OF UNSE'I'I'LING.
( glggleS)

07:02.820 --> 07:05.345
- OKAY.
- BUT I ASSURE YOU,

07:05.450 --> 07:08.010
ONCE WE'VE SIGNED THE PAPERS
I WILL LOOK FORWARD

07:08.120 --> 07:10.224
TO WORKING VERY CLOSE
WITH YOU TO MAKE SURE

07:10.330 --> 07:11.922
OUR BABY IS HEALTHY
AND GETS CONCEIVED.

07:12.030 --> 07:13.520
THANK YOU.

07:13.630 --> 07:16.758
GOSH, I'M EXTRA EXCITED.
AREN'T YOU?

07:16.870 --> 07:20.931
WELL, I THINK
WE'RE ALL VERY EXCITED.

07:21.040 --> 07:24.669
- ARE YOU FINISHED
WITH YOUR EGGS?
- I'M DONE, THANK YOU.

07:24.770 --> 07:27.773
WHEN I SAW THE BUILT-INS,
I FELL TOTALLY IN LOVE,

07:27.880 --> 07:29.677
AND I PUT
MY NAME ON THE LIST.
THE OWNER CALLS ME

07:29.780 --> 07:31.702
YESTERDAY MORNING, HE SAID
I COULD HAVE THE PLACE.

07:31.810 --> 07:33.778
BUT THEN HE CALLED BACK
AN HOUR LATER AND SAID

07:33.880 --> 07:35.871
HE WASN'T RENTING IT,
HE WAS GONNA SELL IT.

07:35.980 --> 07:37.982
- OH, THAT'S SO ANNOYING.
- ( sighs )

07:38.090 --> 07:40.684
WHATEVER, I'LL FIND
A PLACE, I GUESS.

07:40.790 --> 07:43.258
- IT'S ALL GOOD.
- TIME'S UP.

07:43.360 --> 07:45.726
OH, I WAS JUST
FINDING MY RHYTHM.

07:45.830 --> 07:47.923
NEXT WEEK WE START
OUR CAPELETS,

07:48.030 --> 07:51.363
SO PICK OUT
SOME COLORFUL STUFF
AND GET READY.

07:51.470 --> 07:53.665
AND REMEMBER
YOUR CLASS FEES INCLUDE

07:53.770 --> 07:55.829
UNLIMITED KNITTING
CIRCLE TIME,

07:55.940 --> 07:57.999
SO FEEL FREE
TO DROP IN WHENEVER.

07:58.110 --> 08:00.408
- Woman: SEE YOU NEXT TIME.
- CIAO-CIAO, VICTORIA.

08:00.510 --> 08:02.546
CIAO.

08:02.650 --> 08:04.572
SUDDENLY ONE "CIAO"
WAS NOT ENOUGH.

08:04.680 --> 08:07.012
SHE SAYS
EVERYTHING TWICE.

08:07.120 --> 08:08.371
( giggles )

08:08.480 --> 08:10.414
SO...

08:10.520 --> 08:13.683
GIVE US
THE GEORGE REPORT.

08:13.790 --> 08:16.953
WELL, THIS WEEK
HAS NOT BEEN A CAKEWALK

08:17.060 --> 08:18.618
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT A RELIEF IT WAS

08:18.730 --> 08:21.028
TO WALK IN HERE
AND SIT DOWN.

08:21.130 --> 08:22.859
WHAT HAPPENED?

08:22.970 --> 08:25.325
OH, HE STARTED ANOTHER
ROUND OF ELECTROSHOCK,

08:25.430 --> 08:28.638
BECAUSE GEORGE AND MAGGIE
THINK IT HELPS.

08:28.740 --> 08:30.662
BUT THE DAYS
AFTER THE TREATMENTS ARE

08:30.770 --> 08:32.806
SUCH A CHALLENGE FOR ME.

08:32.910 --> 08:36.129
HE COMES HOME SO SCA'I'I'ERED.
IT'S LIKE DEALING
WITH A SLEEPWALKER.

08:36.240 --> 08:39.243
I DON'T KNOW WHERE
YOU FIND THE STRENGTH
TO DEAL WITH IT.

08:39.350 --> 08:41.716
CLEARLY, I DON'T EITHER.

08:41.820 --> 08:44.345
HAVE YOU SIGNED UP
FOR NEXT WEEK'S CLASS?

08:44.450 --> 08:46.281
I HAVEN'T YET, NO.

08:46.390 --> 08:49.484
OH, RUTH, YOU MUST.
YOU'RE THE ONLY VERSION
OF MY MOTHER

08:49.590 --> 08:52.184
- I CAN TALK TO.
- I'LL TRY AND MAKE IT.

08:54.530 --> 08:56.259
IT'S ALL GOOD, RIGHT?

08:56.360 --> 08:58.965
YEAH, IT IS.

09:02.270 --> 09:04.158
WELL, I HAVE
ERRANDS TO RUN,

09:04.270 --> 09:06.875
AND MAGGIE'S WAITING.

09:07.440 --> 09:10.204
Both: BYE.

09:11.210 --> 09:13.519
( chuckles )

09:13.620 --> 09:16.589
( traffic humming )

09:16.690 --> 09:18.817
( whimpers )

09:28.000 --> 09:31.766
LILA WAS
THE MOST ACTIVE PERSON
I EVER MET IN MY LIFE.

09:31.870 --> 09:34.759
I MEAN,
I TRY TO STAY BUSY

09:34.870 --> 09:37.236
WITH BRIDGE
AND THE ANGELS.

09:37.340 --> 09:39.262
I'M A BIG ANGEL FAN.

09:39.370 --> 09:41.736
- I CAN SEE THAT.
- BUT LILA,

09:41.840 --> 09:44.547
SHE WAS
A RUNAWAY TRAIN!

09:44.650 --> 09:46.971
IT'S SO HARD TO BELIEVE
THAT SHE WON'T BE OUTSIDE

09:47.080 --> 09:50.083
MESSING AROUND
WITH HER FLOWERS
WHEN I GET HOME.

09:50.190 --> 09:53.512
ARE YOU SURE
SHE NEVER MARRIED
OR HAD ANY CHILDREN?

09:53.620 --> 09:55.417
OH, SHE WAS GOING TO,

09:55.520 --> 09:58.523
BUT HER BEAU DIED
VERY YOUNG.

09:58.630 --> 10:01.758
AFI'ER THAT
SHE RAN A RESORT

10:01.860 --> 10:04.966
UP IN OJAI
ALL ON HER OWN.

10:05.070 --> 10:07.891
THERE WERE FAMILIES
THAT CAME THERE EVERY YEAR,

10:08.000 --> 10:10.468
AND THEN
THEIR KIDS WOULD COME

10:10.570 --> 10:12.458
AND THEIR KIDS
WOULD COME

10:12.570 --> 10:15.277
AND THEY ALL
KEPT UP WITH HER.

10:15.380 --> 10:17.473
NO ONE
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD

10:17.580 --> 10:20.572
GOT MORE CHRISTMAS CARDS
OR VISITS THAN LILA.

10:20.680 --> 10:24.639
- SOUNDS LIKE A GOOD LIFE.
- IT WAS.

10:24.750 --> 10:28.015
TODAY WOULD HAVE BEEN
HER 95TH BIRTHDAY.

10:28.120 --> 10:29.758
HMM.

10:30.590 --> 10:33.354
WHAT?

10:33.460 --> 10:36.349
WELL, TODAY IS
HIS BIRTHDAY TOO.

10:36.460 --> 10:39.623
OH, HOW OLD ARE YOU?

10:39.740 --> 10:43.437
- I'M 40.
- OH, YOU DON'T LOOK
THAT OLD.

10:43.540 --> 10:45.007
THANK YOU.

10:45.110 --> 10:47.704
- ARE YOU DOING
SOMETHING SPECIAL?
- NOT TODAY,

10:47.810 --> 10:49.698
BUT MY WIFE AND DAUGHTER
ARE GONNA TAKE ME

10:49.810 --> 10:51.641
UP TO BIG SUR
NEXT WEEKEND.

10:51.750 --> 10:54.878
OH. BIG SUR.

10:55.880 --> 10:58.986
IT'S SO BEAUTIFUL
UP THERE.

11:00.260 --> 11:03.889
SO STUNNING!

11:07.930 --> 11:11.127
I SUPPOSE I'LL BE
GONE SOON TOO.

11:11.230 --> 11:13.790
_ OH--
- I WILL.

11:14.770 --> 11:17.364
THAT'S OKAY.

11:18.210 --> 11:20.371
IT HAPPENS.

11:22.780 --> 11:24.304
COULDN'T YOU SAY,
"ROGER, MY PARTNER AND I

11:24.410 --> 11:26.674
PLAN TO SPEND THE MORNING
TOGETHER, I CAN'T PICK UP

11:26.780 --> 11:28.873
- YOUR CAT AT THE VET"?
- DAVID, LET IT GO.

11:28.980 --> 11:30.948
WHY CAN'T HE GET ONE OF HIS
ABERCROMBIE & FITCH

11:31.050 --> 11:33.189
PARTY BOYS TO DO
SOMETHING LIKE THIS?

11:33.290 --> 11:34.917
YOU'RE A BODYGUARD,

11:35.020 --> 11:37.784
AND I'D LIKE
TO GET TO WORK
AT SOME POINT TODAY.

11:37.890 --> 11:39.380
DO YOU LIKE
YOUR NEW PLASMA TV?

11:39.490 --> 11:41.549
( sighs )
I DO.

11:41.660 --> 11:43.662
THEN LET IT GO.

11:43.770 --> 11:46.159
- ( doorbell rings )
- THAT CAT STINKS.

11:46.270 --> 11:48.397
KEITH CHARLES!

11:48.500 --> 11:51.708
- AND YOU MUST BE DAVID!
- YES.

11:51.810 --> 11:53.698
SISSY PASQUESE.

11:53.810 --> 11:56.131
COME ON IN.
ROGER'S MAKING KIR ROYALES.

11:57.980 --> 11:59.277
- SISTER?
- I DON'T KNOW.

11:59.380 --> 12:02.076
- THE KIDS ARE ALMOST READY.
- KIDS? EX-WIFE?

12:02.180 --> 12:04.387
- I DON'T KNOW!
- HOW COULD YOU NOT KNOW?

12:04.490 --> 12:06.446
DAVID,
WE'RE MARRIED,

12:06.550 --> 12:07.983
ROGER'S GAY,
AND I'M FINE WITH IT.

12:08.090 --> 12:11.025
BUT WE KEEP IT QUIET,
BECAUSE WE'RE VERY
PRIVATE PEOPLE.

12:11.130 --> 12:13.394
THANK YOU.

12:13.500 --> 12:16.458
- THAT'S ALL I NEEDED.
- HONEY, GUESS WHO'S HERE.

12:16.560 --> 12:19.222
- ( machinery humming )
- ( phone ringing )

12:24.740 --> 12:26.662
- HELLO.
- Woman: Mr. Diaz?

12:26.780 --> 12:28.475
YES, WHO IS THIS?

12:28.580 --> 12:31.105
AGNES, I WORK
FOR THE CAMPBELLS.

12:31.210 --> 12:32.746
JULIO CAME HOME
WITH LUCAS AFTER SCHOOL.

12:32.850 --> 12:34.943
Oh. Yeah?

12:35.050 --> 12:37.041
WELL, HE KIND OF NEEDS
TO BE PICKED UP.

12:37.150 --> 12:39.983
OH, OKAY,
MY WIFE VAN ESSA

12:40.090 --> 12:41.819
SHOULD BE THERE
IN A LITTLE BIT, I THINK.

12:41.920 --> 12:43.956
No, we called her
like 10 times,

12:44.060 --> 12:46.028
and she's not answering
her phone or something,

12:46.130 --> 12:49.998
and the Campbells left
for Arrowhead like
an hour ago.

12:50.100 --> 12:52.364
I'M SORRY.
I'LL BE RIGHT OVER.

12:54.140 --> 12:56.665
- ( purring )
- AND I TOLD ROGER
10 YEARS AGO,

12:56.770 --> 12:58.931
"ROGER, I WANT OUT
OF THIS GODDAMN L.A.

12:59.040 --> 13:01.133
IT'S A PLAGUE.
I WANT TO GO HOME."

13:01.240 --> 13:04.505
- ( jazz music playing )
- I HAVEN'T BEEN
BACK HERE SINCE,

13:04.610 --> 13:06.840
sEEXCEPT FOR TWO-DAY TRIP,
THREE-DAY TRIPS, RIGHT?

13:06.950 --> 13:08.747
I MISS HER
WHEN SHE'S GONE.

13:08.850 --> 13:11.148
I'M AN ASPEN GIRL,
WHAT CAN I SAY?

13:11.250 --> 13:13.013
SO, WHAT BRINGS YOU
TO TOWN?

13:13.120 --> 13:15.953
A PEDUNCULATED FIBROID.

13:16.060 --> 13:18.756
SHIT FOR ME, HUH?

13:18.860 --> 13:22.023
AND TATE AND ENZO
NEED HAIRCUTS.

13:22.130 --> 13:25.224
SO, ROGER TELLS ME
YOU TWO ARE THINKING
OF ADOPTING.

13:25.330 --> 13:27.469
LOOKS LIKE THAT'S NOT
HAPPENING ANYMORE.

13:27.570 --> 13:30.232
BECAUSE YOU BIT ROGER?

13:30.340 --> 13:32.501
NO.

13:32.610 --> 13:33.907
IT GOT COMPLICATED.

13:34.010 --> 13:36.069
SHIT FOR YOU GUYS, HUH?

13:38.110 --> 13:40.510
KEITH, YOU THINK
YOU COULD RUN THE KIDS
BY LAISSEZ-FAIRE

13:40.620 --> 13:42.611
WHILE I TAKE SISSY
TO THE DOCTOR?

13:42.720 --> 13:44.210
UH, WE ACTUALLY
HAVE AN ERRAND

13:44.320 --> 13:47.050
THAT WE NEED TO RUN
AT SOME POINT.

13:48.290 --> 13:51.327
IT'S ON THE WAY.
WE'LL TAKE THEM.

13:51.430 --> 13:53.898
Roger: THANKS.

13:54.000 --> 13:55.956
HONEY, THE CAT
STILL REEKS.

13:56.060 --> 13:59.268
Roger:
I KNOW, I KNOW.

13:59.370 --> 14:02.294
Jackie: PEOPLE DO THINGS
FOR OTHER PEOPLE.
THAT'S OKAY.

14:02.400 --> 14:04.038
WELL, I DON'T WANT HIM
TO DO IT JUST FOR ME.

14:04.140 --> 14:06.108
- WHY THE HELL NOT?
- BECAUSE I WANT HIM

14:06.210 --> 14:08.030
TO WANT TO HAVE
OUR BABY,

14:08.140 --> 14:09.801
NOT TO DO ME THE FAVOR
OF LE'I'I'ING ME HAVE MINE.

14:09.910 --> 14:12.504
DON'T BE WEIRDER
ABOUT THIS THAN YOU
ABSOLUTELY HAVE TO BE.

14:12.610 --> 14:14.510
BUT HE SHOULD
WANT TO HAVE THIS
AS MUCH AS I DO.

14:14.620 --> 14:16.815
- HE HAS MAYA ALREADY.
- NO, IT'S NOT THE SAME THING.

14:16.920 --> 14:18.979
THEN MAYBE HE'S AFRAID
OF LOSING ANOTHER ONE.

14:19.090 --> 14:20.819
YOU KNOW?
AND ANYWAY,

14:20.920 --> 14:23.787
LET'S SAY HE IS
DOING IT JUST FOR YOU.
IS THAT SO TERRIBLE?

14:23.890 --> 14:25.687
WE HAD SYLVIA

14:25.790 --> 14:28.020
FOR ALL THE PERFECT
BOTH-OF-US REASONS,

14:28.130 --> 14:30.121
AND I HAD JOSH FOR MARK,

14:30.230 --> 14:32.892
BECAUSE HE COULDN'T IMAGINE
LIFE WITHOUT A BOY.

14:33.000 --> 14:35.230
I WAS HAPPY WITH ONE.

14:37.040 --> 14:38.860
CAN YOU NOT TELL ANYONE
ABOUT THE PREGNANCY?

14:38.970 --> 14:40.528
- FUCK YOU.
- NO, I WANT
TO WAIT THIS TIME

14:40.640 --> 14:42.904
UNTIL I KNOW
EVERYTHING IS GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT.

14:43.010 --> 14:44.875
BRENDA, STOP.

14:44.980 --> 14:47.619
I SWEAR, SOMETIMES YOU'RE
LIKE EEYORE.

14:47.720 --> 14:49.676
CHECK IT OUT.

14:49.780 --> 14:51.611
OH, THAT'S A GOOD ONE.

14:51.720 --> 14:55.087
10,000 TO GO.

14:55.190 --> 14:57.226
Agnes:
BUT JASON IS ONLY IN TOWN
FOR TONIGHT, CHARESE.

14:57.330 --> 14:59.423
YOU HAVE TO BE THERE,
ALL RIGHT?

14:59.530 --> 15:02.226
YOU HAVE TO!
HE JUST GOT DONE WITH BASIC,

15:02.330 --> 15:04.764
AND HE'S GOING, LIKE,
IN TWO DAYS!

15:04.870 --> 15:06.895
THEN GET OFF WORK.

15:07.000 --> 15:09.139
I'M TRYING!

15:09.240 --> 15:11.834
I'M LEAVING
AS SOON AS I CAN.

15:11.940 --> 15:13.498
DON'T GET A TONE
WITH ME

15:13.610 --> 15:15.771
WHEN YOU CAN'T EVEN GET
YOUR BUT!" OUT OF PIZZA HUT.

15:15.880 --> 15:18.678
OH, HEY, MR. DIAZ.
NO, I SAID THE 110.

15:18.780 --> 15:20.941
- COME ON, LET'S GO HOME.
- THE 110 TO THE 710.

15:21.050 --> 15:22.711
STOP FOR A SECOND
AND LISTEN TO ME.

15:22.820 --> 15:25.186
I'M GIVING YOU
THE DIRECTIONS.
