28:54.260 --> 28:57.457
BIRDS DON'T
USUALLY FLY AT NIGHT.
IT'S PROBABLY SICK.

28:57.560 --> 28:59.892
DO YOU THINK
IT HAS AVIAN FLU?

29:00.000 --> 29:03.163
OBVIOUSLY, WE DON'T KNOW.
JUST OPEN THE WINDOW,

29:03.270 --> 29:05.204
CLOSE THE DOOR,
AND IT'LL FIND
ITS OWN WAY OUT.

29:05.310 --> 29:07.835
- BUT HE'LL POOP ALL OVER
EVERYTHING IRVUTTH'T MEANTIME.

29:07.940 --> 29:09.498
WELL, SERIOUSLY,
WHAT KIND OF PLAN IS THAT,

29:09.610 --> 29:11.976
TO LET A SICK BIRD
RUN WILD IN THE HOUSE
POOPING?

29:12.080 --> 29:15.174
YOU KNOW WHAT, MOM?
I THINK GEORGE IS RIGHT.
I AM JUST GONNA...

29:15.280 --> 29:17.339
OPEN THE WINDOW.

29:17.450 --> 29:20.886
- ( cawing )
- I'M GONNA OPEN THIS DOOR.

29:23.790 --> 29:27.055
SOMEBODY CLOSE THAT DOOR.

29:27.160 --> 29:29.856
- HEY, NATE,
GRAB THE BEER, OKAY?
- YEAH, I'LL GRAB THE BEER, TOM.

29:29.960 --> 29:31.825
- THANK YOU.
- David: IT'S
A BEAUTIFUL BIRD.

29:31.930 --> 29:35.093
GOD, IT'S FUCKING
CERULEAN.

29:35.200 --> 29:39.534
SO LET'S JUST
CLOSE THIS DOOR

29:39.640 --> 29:41.608
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

29:41.710 --> 29:43.905
( cawing )

29:46.350 --> 29:47.647
JESUS.

29:47.750 --> 29:51.208
- THANKS FOR
LETTING ME STAY.
- SURE.

29:51.320 --> 29:54.858
I HAVEN'T PUT THE BOYS
TO BED FOR AWHILE.

29:54.960 --> 29:56.951
I MISS THAT.

29:57.060 --> 29:59.881
YEAH, THEY MISS IT TOO.

30:13.610 --> 30:17.478
( rock music
playing faintly)

30:17.580 --> 30:19.639
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

30:19.750 --> 30:21.615
I GOTTA GET THE FUCK
OUT OF HERE.

30:21.720 --> 30:23.449
WHY?

30:23.550 --> 30:26.781
I JUST DO.
WE'LL CRUISE MULHOLLAND.
WE'LL GO TO THE LOOKOUT.

30:26.890 --> 30:28.482
NO, I DON'T WANT
TO GO.

30:28.590 --> 30:31.320
IT'S MY BROTHER'S BIRTHDAY.
THERE'S A BIRD IN THE KITCHEN.

30:31.430 --> 30:34.354
ISN'T BEING WITH OTHER
PEOPLE EVER TOO MUCH
FOR YOU TO DEAL WITH?

30:34.460 --> 30:36.599
YEAH, LIKE RIGHT NOW.

30:38.830 --> 30:40.695
( cawing )

30:40.800 --> 30:42.392
( feathers ruffling )

30:42.500 --> 30:44.365
LOOK, THERE IT IS.

30:44.470 --> 30:46.768
- David: SHOO IT
OUT THE WINDOW.
- Keith: WAIT A SECOND.

30:46.870 --> 30:49.839
- DON'T TOUCH IT.
- DAVID, SHUT UP.

31:03.590 --> 31:05.626
GOOD JOB.

31:09.530 --> 31:12.863
- YOU'RE NOT COMING?
- NO, I ALREADY
TOLD YOU THAT.

31:13.830 --> 31:16.162
HERE.
YOU KEEP THE CAR.

31:16.270 --> 31:19.000
- YOU CAN'T WALK HOME.
- WELL, IF IT'S TOO FAR,
I'LL TAKE A CAB.

31:19.110 --> 31:22.534
STOP IT! JUST RELAX
AND STAY, PLEASE.

31:22.640 --> 31:24.301
I WANT YOU TO STAY.

31:24.410 --> 31:27.106
PLEASE.

31:35.420 --> 31:38.025
ALL RIGHT.

31:38.130 --> 31:40.849
- BUT JUST FOR
A LITTLE WHILE, OKAY?
- FINE.

31:40.960 --> 31:43.394
FUCKING-- FUCK!

31:43.500 --> 31:45.491
SHIT! GOD!

31:45.600 --> 31:47.693
FUCK! SHIT!

31:47.800 --> 31:49.688
IT'S JUST A BIRD.
WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM?

31:49.800 --> 31:51.563
I'M JUST KINDA
FREAKED OUT BY THINGS

31:51.670 --> 31:54.468
THAT ARE MOVING AROUND
THAT I CAN'T CONTROL.

31:54.580 --> 31:57.174
IT'S NOT A PROBLEM.

31:57.280 --> 31:59.168
DID YOU STOP TAKING
YOUR MEDICATION?

31:59.280 --> 32:02.738
YEAH, BUT THAT'S
A GOOD THING.

32:02.850 --> 32:06.946
- WHY?
- BECAUSE, CLAIRE,
OKAY,

32:07.050 --> 32:09.109
I'M SICK OF FEELING
LIKE I'M LIVING EVERY MOMENT

32:09.220 --> 32:13.725
INSIDE A GIANT XEROXED
FUCKING COTTON BALL.

32:13.830 --> 32:16.458
- I GOTTA GO OUTSIDE.
- NO, DON'T GO.

32:16.560 --> 32:19.597
I'M JUST GOING OUTSIDE.
WILL YOU FUCKING LISTEN
WHEN I TALK?

32:19.700 --> 32:21.964
- HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?
- I'M JUST GOING OUTSIDE.

32:22.070 --> 32:25.665
- Billy: JESUS CHRIST.
- WHAT THE FUCK IS GOING ON?

32:25.770 --> 32:27.306
NOTHING.
EVERYTHING IS FINE.

32:27.410 --> 32:29.878
- HE DIDN'T JUST
HIT YOU, DID HE?
- NO.

32:29.980 --> 32:32.301
WOULD YOU PLEASE STOP
BEING SUCH A FREAK?

32:32.410 --> 32:34.378
BY THE WAY, THE BIRD
IS IN THE BEDROOM NOW.

32:34.480 --> 32:36.710
YEAH, WELL, HOW DID
THE BIRD GET IN
THE BEDROOM?

32:36.820 --> 32:39.414
IT FLEW IN THE DOOR.
STOP FUCKING UP.

32:39.520 --> 32:43.149
SHE USED TO BE THE WIFE
ON THAT BIG FAT HUSBAND SHOW.

32:43.260 --> 32:46.388
- WHICH ONE?
- "MORE FOR ME."

32:46.490 --> 32:48.424
ARE YOU SURE THIS IS
THE SAME VICTORIA ADAMS?

32:48.530 --> 32:51.920
OH, YEAH YEAH,
THAT SHOW WAS A HUGE HIT
FOR SEVEN YEARS,

32:52.030 --> 32:54.260
AND THEN WHEN THEY FINALLY
SHUT DOWN,

32:54.370 --> 32:57.396
- SHE OPENED
THAT KNITTING STORE.
- SHE NEVER MENTIONS IT.

32:57.500 --> 33:00.708
WELL, THEN I BET
SHE STILL DOES THAT
WINKING THING, RIGHT?

33:00.810 --> 33:02.505
SHE DOES DO THAT
WINKING THING.

33:02.610 --> 33:06.876
WELL, THAT WAS HER THING
ON THE SHOW, YEAH.

33:06.980 --> 33:08.948
- HEY, ARE YOU OKAY?
- Brenda: OH, YEAH.

33:09.050 --> 33:11.746
"MAX THE POET,
AND HE'S THE DOG."

33:11.850 --> 33:15.513
- WHAT ARE YOU READING?
- WE ARE READING A BOOK ABOUT
A DOG WHO IS ALSO A POET.

33:15.620 --> 33:17.986
- EXCUSE ME.
- Keith: YOU ARE? GREAT.

33:18.090 --> 33:21.355
David:
YEAH, DOGGIE
DOGGIE DOGGIE.

33:21.460 --> 33:25.191
- HE'S A DOG.
- Maya: YEP YEP.

33:25.300 --> 33:28.189
BY THE WAY,
JUST FOR THE RECORD,

33:28.300 --> 33:30.837
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
SISSY PASQUESE MEANS
WHEN SHE SAYS "PRIVATE,"

33:30.940 --> 33:34.068
BUT THOSE KIDS
OF HERS KNOW WAY TOO
MUCH ABOUT EVERYTHING.

33:34.180 --> 33:36.205
I THINK IT'S NICE THEY'VE
BEEN GIVEN SOME PERSPECTIVE.

33:36.310 --> 33:38.301
YEAH, IN EXCHANGE
FOR A CHILDHOOD.

33:38.410 --> 33:40.799
WHATEVER WE DO,
WE'RE NOT GONNA PUT
OUR KIDS THROUGH THAT.

33:40.910 --> 33:45.188
PARENTS CAN HAVE
A FEW SECRETS.
IT'S NOT A BAD THING.

33:45.290 --> 33:47.884
- I'M SERIOUS.
- FINE. WE'LL HAVE SECRETS.

33:47.990 --> 33:50.288
YOU GOT IT.

33:50.390 --> 33:52.620
OKAY.

33:52.730 --> 33:57.451
"PARIS, THE CITY OF DREAMS,
THE CITY OF LIGHTS,

33:57.560 --> 33:59.596
THE CITY OF LOVE."

33:59.700 --> 34:02.430
( moaning )

34:07.070 --> 34:09.436
SHH SHH SHH.
YOU'RE GONNA WAKE THE BOYS.

34:09.540 --> 34:12.247
NO, THEY SLEEP
THROUGH IT NOW.

34:16.080 --> 34:18.310
OKAY.

34:22.790 --> 34:25.122
( rock music playing )

34:29.630 --> 34:31.564
IS THIS THE LINE T0 PEE?

34:31.670 --> 34:34.059
YEP.

34:37.900 --> 34:40.232
SO THE BIRD'S
IN THERE NOW?

34:40.340 --> 34:42.137
- YEAH.
- HOW'D IT GET IN THERE?

34:42.240 --> 34:45.801
- I DON'T KNOW.
- WHAT DID YOU SAY TO BILLY?
HE WAS REALLY UPSET.

34:45.910 --> 34:48.708
I DIDN'T SAY
ANYTHING TO BILLY. HE HAD
SOME THING WITH CLAIRE,

34:48.820 --> 34:51.983
- HE GOT MAD
AND HE WALKED OUT.
- WELL, WHAT HAPPENED?

34:52.090 --> 34:53.842
YOU KNOW, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED, BRENDA.

34:53.950 --> 34:56.748
I GUESS WHAT USUALLY
HAPPENS. YOUR BROTHER
WENT FUCKING MENTAL.

34:56.860 --> 34:59.988
HEY, YOU MIGHT WANT
TO WAIT A FEW SECONDS
BEFORE YOU GO IN THERE.

35:00.090 --> 35:02.399
( laughs )

35:02.500 --> 35:03.592
THAN KS.

35:03.700 --> 35:06.191
WHY DID YOU FUCKING
INVITE THAT GUY?

35:06.300 --> 35:08.188
- I THOUGHT HE
WAS YOUR FRIEND.
- HE'S NOT.

35:08.300 --> 35:10.689
- YOU KNOW,
IT REALLY--
- EXCUSE ME.

35:13.670 --> 35:15.809
I HATE THAT YOU'RE ALWAYS
JUMPING TO CONCLUSIONS
ABOUT BILLY.

35:15.910 --> 35:19.209
- YOU WILL NEVER BELIEVE
THAT HE'S GETTING BETTER.
- NO, I WON'T.

35:19.310 --> 35:21.619
I HATE THAT HE'S
WITH CLAIRE AND IN
OUR FUCKING HOUSE.

35:21.720 --> 35:23.711
YEAH, WELL, AT LEAST
HE KNOWS HOW TO KEEP
A SECRET.

35:23.820 --> 35:26.516
LOOK, I KNOW THAT YOU
TOLD JACKIE, SO WHAT'S
THE BIG FUCKING DEAL?

35:26.620 --> 35:29.714
THERE IS A VERY BIG
DIFFERENCE BETWEEN ME
TELLING MY SUPERVISOR,

35:29.820 --> 35:32.027
AND YOU TELLING OUR
ENTIRE FAMILY, WHO ARE
NOW LOOKING AT ME

35:32.130 --> 35:35.099
- WONDERING WHEN I'M GONNA
LOSE THIS BABY.
- JESUS CHRIST!

35:35.200 --> 35:38.966
- THIS MORNING I WASN'T EXCITED
ENOUGH, NOW I'M TOO EXCITED.
- NO, THAT WASN'T EXCITEMENT.

35:39.070 --> 35:43.063
- THAT WAS MACHO,
AGGRESSIVE MALE BULLSHIT.
- WHAT THE FUCK IS THIS?

35:43.170 --> 35:46.662
- IT MAKES ME WONDER
IF WE SHOULD BE TOGETHER.
- WE JUST GOT MARRIED.

35:46.770 --> 35:50.638
YEAH, WELL, IF IT'S NOT
RIGHT, IT'S NOT RIGHT.

35:50.740 --> 35:55.109
YOU MIGHT WANT TO LIGHT
A MATCH IN THERE.
IT WASN'T ME.

35:55.220 --> 35:58.712
YOU'RE FREAKED OUT RIGHT NOW
BECAUSE YOU'RE PREGNANT.
YOU SEE THAT, DON'T YOU?

35:58.820 --> 36:00.549
YEAH, WITH A BABY
THAT YOU DON'T EVEN WANT.

36:00.650 --> 36:02.789
- BULLSHIT!
- YOU DON'T
RESPECT ME ENOUGH

36:02.890 --> 36:04.721
TO WAIT UNTIL WE KNOW THAT
EVERYTHING'S ALL RIGHT

36:04.830 --> 36:07.025
- BEFORE YOU TELL
THE WHOLE WORLD.
- SHUT THE FUCK UP!

36:07.130 --> 36:09.758
I NEED TO PEE.

36:15.400 --> 36:17.595
Jackie and Tom:
NATE!

36:17.700 --> 36:19.634
YEAH?

36:20.640 --> 36:23.803
TEQUILA SHOTS
IN THE KITCHEN.

36:23.910 --> 36:25.639
( man yelling )

36:25.750 --> 36:27.809
GET IN HERE!

36:33.050 --> 36:34.813
SO YOU STOPPED TAKING IT?

36:34.920 --> 36:37.684
- JUST LIKE THAT?
- YEAH.

36:40.360 --> 36:43.397
AND YOU FEEL...?

36:43.500 --> 36:46.298
I FEEL A LITTLE TINGLY.

36:46.400 --> 36:49.528
THAT'S ABOUT IT.

36:49.640 --> 36:51.699
WHAT DO THEY GOT
YOU ON THESE DAYS?

36:51.810 --> 36:54.370
WELL, THEY JUST SWITCHED ME
FROM LITHIUM TO TOFRANIL,

36:54.480 --> 36:57.699
IN BETWEEN
THE SHOCK TREATMENTS.

36:59.350 --> 37:01.818
WHAT ARE THOSE LIKE?

37:01.920 --> 37:07.313
HON ESTLY. ..
I DON'T KNOW.

37:07.420 --> 37:10.583
I GO IN.
THEY PUT ME ON A BED.
THEY GIVE ME SOME OXYGEN.

37:10.690 --> 37:14.251
THEY SAY, "YOU'RE GONNA FEEL
A LITTLE PRICK IN YOUR HAND."
THAT ALWAYS MAKES ME LAUGH.

37:14.360 --> 37:16.555
AND THEN THE NEXT THING
I KNOW I WAKE UP

37:16.660 --> 37:18.821
WITH THE WORST HEADACHE
I'VE EVER HAD IN MY LIFE.

37:23.640 --> 37:25.858
DO YOU THINK IT'S HELPING?

37:25.970 --> 37:29.269
I THINK THAT...

37:29.380 --> 37:31.974
AS MILE COU USED TO SAY,

37:32.080 --> 37:36.744
"EVERY DAY IN EVERY WAY,
I AM GETTING BETTER
AND BETTER."

37:38.890 --> 37:41.381
BUT NOT EVERYONE AGREES.

37:41.490 --> 37:43.549
YEAH, IT'S HARD TO GET
YOUR SHIT TOGETHER

37:43.660 --> 37:45.753
WITH SOMEONE WATCHING
ALL THE TIME.

37:45.860 --> 37:48.351
YEAH, IT IS.

37:48.460 --> 37:51.463
BUT WHEN NO ONE'S WATCHING,
THEN WHERE ARE YOU?

37:51.570 --> 37:53.925
WHERE THE FUCK
ARE YOU THEN?

38:00.940 --> 38:04.808
* DADDY SANG BASS

38:04.910 --> 38:07.470
* MAMA SANG TENOR

38:07.580 --> 38:10.743
* ME AND LITTLE BROTHER
WOULD JOIN RIGHT IN THERE *

38:10.850 --> 38:16.755
* SINGIN' SEEMED TO HELP
A TROUBLED SOUL... *

38:23.860 --> 38:25.669
I'M GONNA TAKE OFF.

38:25.770 --> 38:28.637
- OKAY.
- WHY DON'T YOU GIVE
THESE TO CLAIRE?

38:28.740 --> 38:31.129
- YEAH, SURE.
- THANKS.

38:31.240 --> 38:33.538
HAPPY BIRTH DAY.

38:33.640 --> 38:36.234
I MEAN, IT'S NICE
TO SEE YOU.

38:36.340 --> 38:38.672
YEAH.

38:49.320 --> 38:51.185
Brenda:
"LOUIE'S WEARING
THE GREEN HAT."

38:51.290 --> 38:53.178
- WHO'S THAT?
- Maya: LOUIS.

38:53.290 --> 38:55.053
LOUIS. THAT'S RIGHT.

38:55.160 --> 38:57.799
HEY.

38:57.900 --> 39:00.562
HEY.

39:00.670 --> 39:03.138
YOU MUST BE LOOKING FORWARD
TO THIS ROUTINE.

39:03.240 --> 39:05.959
YEAH, I THINK IT'S
GONNA BE WONDERFUL.

39:06.070 --> 39:07.662
OH, COME ON.

39:07.770 --> 39:10.568
WHO'S GOT ON
THE BLUE COAT?

39:12.450 --> 39:14.509
- WHO'S THAT?
- BEAR.

39:14.620 --> 39:17.976
- THE BEAR, THE BEAR.
- THE BEAR.

39:21.860 --> 39:24.920
FOR SO MANY YEARS,
DAVID WAS ALWAYS
THE ONE SAYING,

39:25.030 --> 39:26.759
"COME ON,
LET'S HAVE KIDS."

39:26.860 --> 39:29.158
AND I WAS THE ONE
ON THE FENCE,

39:29.260 --> 39:31.228
BUT NOW THAT IT'S
ACTUALLY GONNA HAPPEN,

39:31.330 --> 39:36.063
I'M FINALLY REALIZING THAT
I'M GONNA BE DISAPPOINTED
IF IT DOESN'T WORK OUT.

39:36.170 --> 39:37.831
OH, IT'LL WORK OUT.

39:37.940 --> 39:41.501
IT'S LIKE I'M ALREADY MISSING
THIS KID THAT WE DON'T
EVEN HAVE YET.

39:41.610 --> 39:44.135
I MEAN, DON'T GET ME WRONG,
DAVID'S EXCITED TOO.

39:44.240 --> 39:46.970
OH, YEAH, YOU KNOW,
NATE TOO.

39:47.080 --> 39:49.776
IT'S A TEAM EFFORT.

39:51.920 --> 39:54.115
I'LL LET YOU GUYS
HAVE YOUR MOMENT.

39:54.220 --> 39:55.653
SAY "GOOD NIGHT,
UNCLE KEITH."

39:55.760 --> 39:59.025
- GOOD NIGHT, UNCLE KEITH.
- GOOD NIGHT.

39:59.130 --> 40:00.825
ARE YOU SLEEPY,
LITTLE ONE?

40:00.930 --> 40:03.251
- COULD YOU TURN
THE LIGHT OFF?
- OH, YEAH, SURE.

40:03.360 --> 40:05.169
AND CLOSE THE DOOR, THANKS.

40:05.270 --> 40:07.192
OKAY, LITTLE ONE,

40:07.300 --> 40:09.939
I THINK
THAT'S ENOUGH FOR TONIGHT.

40:10.040 --> 40:13.032
MM, RASPBERRY.

40:15.310 --> 40:17.676
EVERYTHING TASTES
LIKE BEER RIGHT NOW.

40:21.380 --> 40:22.847
- HEY.
- HEY.

40:22.950 --> 40:25.009
HEY.

40:25.120 --> 40:26.519
GEORGE TOLD ME

40:26.620 --> 40:29.350
THAT BILLY TOLD HIM
TO TELL YOU TO GIVE YOU THESE.

40:29.460 --> 40:31.189
BILLY LEFT?

40:31.290 --> 40:33.952
THAT'S WHAT GEORGE SAID.

40:35.730 --> 40:37.550
I'M SORRY.
YOU WANT SOME CAKE?

40:37.660 --> 40:39.469
- NO.
- COME ON, HAVE SOME.

40:39.570 --> 40:43.666
- HEY, DUDE, LEAVE HER ALONE.
- I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF,
THANKS.

40:45.340 --> 40:47.137
LOOKS LIKE
IT'S CAKE TIME.

40:47.240 --> 40:49.037
I'VE BEEN SAVING UP
FOR THIS.

40:49.140 --> 40:52.701
OOH, GOOD.

40:52.810 --> 40:55.779
FUCK. ALL RIGHT, FINE,
I'LL HAVE A PIECE.

40:56.620 --> 40:59.544
HERE YOU GO.

41:14.270 --> 41:17.239
- ( sighs )
- I'M IN HERE.

41:17.340 --> 41:19.399
- HEY.
- SORRY.

41:19.510 --> 41:22.399
NO, THAT'S OKAY.
IT'S COOL.

41:22.510 --> 41:25.104
I JUST NEEDED A MOMENT.

41:25.210 --> 41:28.247
YEAH, ME, TOO.

41:28.350 --> 41:30.318
IS IT GONE?

41:30.420 --> 41:33.480
- YEAH.
- FINALLY.

41:33.590 --> 41:36.582
YOU KNOW, MOM AND GEORGE,
THEY LEFT.

41:36.690 --> 41:38.783
I'M GETTING A RIDE
FROM KEITH AND DAVID.

41:38.890 --> 41:40.755
OH.

41:43.800 --> 41:45.392
TEQUILA?

41:45.500 --> 41:47.923
SURE.

41:52.270 --> 41:54.204
THAN KS.

42:01.150 --> 42:03.277
( speaking Spanish )

42:08.150 --> 42:09.879
IM PRESSIVE.

42:09.990 --> 42:13.027
YEAH, MANY YEARS
IN ARIZONA, MUCH TEQUILA.

42:13.130 --> 42:14.950
OH.

42:17.660 --> 42:19.992
GOOD BIRTH DAY?

42:20.100 --> 42:22.591
YEAH, IT'S OKAY.

42:25.910 --> 42:27.605
FEEL LIKE ALL I CAN
GET OUT OF THIS BIRTHDAY

42:27.710 --> 42:30.679
IS THAT LIFE
IS REALLY FUCKING LONELY.

42:32.280 --> 42:35.477
YOU HAVE THIS
WONDERFUL FAMILY

42:35.580 --> 42:38.708
- AND A BABY ON THE WAY.
- I KNOW.

42:41.020 --> 42:43.284
AND IT'S REALLY
FUCKING LONELY.

42:47.630 --> 42:50.952
I JUST FEEL LIKE
ALL I DO ALL DAY LONG

42:51.060 --> 42:53.460
IS MANAGE MYSELF,

42:53.570 --> 42:57.995
TRY TO FUCKING CONNECT
WITH PEOPLE.

42:58.100 --> 43:00.034
BUT IT'S LIKE NO MATTER
HOW MUCH ENERGY

43:00.140 --> 43:03.974
YOU POUR INTO GETTING
TO THE STATION ON TIME

43:04.080 --> 43:06.048
OR GETTING
ON THE RIGHT TIN,

43:06.150 --> 43:09.313
THERE'S STILL NO FUCKING
GUARANTEE THAT ANYBODY'S
GONNA BE THERE FOR YOU

43:09.420 --> 43:13.015
TO PICK YOU UP
WHEN YOU GET THERE.

43:15.490 --> 43:17.913
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

43:20.090 --> 43:23.594
WELL, I KNOW THAT
IF YOU THINK LIFE'S
A VENDING MACHINE,

43:23.700 --> 43:26.589
WHERE YOU PUT IN VIRTUE

43:26.700 --> 43:28.839
AND YOU GET OUT HAPPINESS,

43:28.940 --> 43:31.659
THEN YOU'RE PROBABLY
GONNA BE DISAPPOINTED.

43:34.010 --> 43:36.035
I KNOW THAT.

43:41.480 --> 43:44.074
IS THAT HOW I SOUND?

43:44.180 --> 43:46.114
A LITTLE.

43:52.890 --> 43:55.859
Brenda:
NATE! NATE!
GET IN HERE!

43:55.960 --> 43:59.088
- FUCK!
- Tom: I DON'T THINK
BELIEVE IT.

43:59.200 --> 44:01.589
Jackie:
OH MY GOD!

44:01.700 --> 44:04.362
WELL, HOW THE FUCK
DID IT GET IN AGAIN?

44:04.470 --> 44:07.064
- THROUGH THE WINDOW.
- YEAH, WHY WAS THE WINDOW OPEN?

44:07.170 --> 44:11.231
'CAUSE YOU SAID
IT WAS IN THE BEDROOM.
DON'T BE SUCH A JERK.

44:11.340 --> 44:13.501
FUCK OFF.

44:13.610 --> 44:16.010
I HAVE TO DO EVERY
LITTLE FUCKING THING MYSELF.

44:18.580 --> 44:20.445
I HAVE TRIED
ALL NIGHT LONG

44:20.550 --> 44:22.381
TO DO THE RIGHT THING
BY THIS BIRD,

44:22.490 --> 44:25.152
BUT IT JUST KEEPS
FUCKING WITH ME.

44:25.260 --> 44:27.979
- TRY NOT TO
TAKE IT PERSONALLY.
- SHUT UP, DAVID.

44:28.090 --> 44:31.423
- ( bird squawking )
- Brenda: NATE!

44:31.530 --> 44:32.827
GET OUT!

44:32.930 --> 44:36.161
Tom:
JESUS CHRIST, CHILL.

44:38.040 --> 44:42.136
- ( glass shatters )
- GET THE MOTHERFUCK OUT!

44:42.240 --> 44:46.142
HOW MANY TIMES DO I
HAVE TO FUCKING APOLOGIZE?

44:47.080 --> 44:48.911
SORRY.

44:49.020 --> 44:52.911
I'M SO SORRY
THAT I'M PUTTING YOU
THROUGH ALL OF THIS.

44:53.020 --> 44:55.113
- IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.
I KNOW THAT.
- NO, YOU DON'T.

44:55.220 --> 44:58.257
YOU SAY THAT YOU DO,
BUT I CAN TELL BY THE WAY
YOU LOOK AT ME,

44:58.360 --> 45:02.251
YOU THINK THAT ALL
OF THIS IS MY FAULT.

45:02.360 --> 45:05.329
YOU DON'T WANNA
MAKE LOVE TO ME.
YOU DON'T WANNA KISS ME.

45:05.430 --> 45:08.467
- YOU DON'T WANNA BE
IN THE SAME ROOM WITH ME!
- THAT'S NOT TRUE.

45:08.570 --> 45:11.459
OH, YES, IT IS!

45:11.570 --> 45:13.208
RUTH...

45:13.310 --> 45:16.199
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND?

45:16.310 --> 45:19.871
NOBODY GROWS UP THINKING
THIS IS THE WAY THEY'RE
GONNA TURN OUT TO BE.

45:19.980 --> 45:23.848
IF I COULD CHANGE
JUST BY SNAPPING MY FINGERS,

45:23.950 --> 45:26.612
- I'D DO IT.
- I KNOW YOU WOULD, GEORGE.

45:26.720 --> 45:28.608
I AM TRYING...

45:28.720 --> 45:32.178
SO HARD TO GET BETTER.

45:32.290 --> 45:35.259
- AND YOU ARE.
- BUT NOT FAST ENOUGH
FOR YOU!

45:35.360 --> 45:39.262
YOU'RE GETTING BETTER
AS FAST AS YOU CAN.
I KNOW THAT.

45:39.370 --> 45:41.838
I AM SO LUCKY.

45:41.940 --> 45:45.159
I HATE THAT I'M
THE LUCKY ONE.

45:48.980 --> 45:51.403
NO ONE'S EVER LUCKY
TO HAVE ME.

45:53.980 --> 45:57.143
NOBODY'S EVER BEEN
LUCKY TO HAVE ME.

46:01.450 --> 46:03.884
( rock music playing )

46:29.720 --> 46:32.188
IT'S GOOD, RIGHT?

46:54.110 --> 46:56.908
- RICO, WAKE UP.
- ( mumbles )

46:57.010 --> 47:00.343
BABY, HURRY UP.
YOU GOTTA GET OUT OF HERE.

47:00.450 --> 47:02.270
WHY?

47:02.380 --> 47:06.146
I DON'T WANT
THE BOYS TO SEE YOU.
IT'LL CONFUSE THEM.

47:08.150 --> 47:10.289
OH.

47:12.630 --> 47:14.586
ALL RIGHT.

47:16.930 --> 47:17.828
- I know there's
beautiful snow there--
- David: NO, THAT'S GREAT.

47:17.930 --> 47:19.727
I JUST, YOU KNOW...

47:19.830 --> 47:21.559
THANK YOU.

47:21.670 --> 47:24.389
OKAY, BYE.

47:24.500 --> 47:25.865
WHO WAS THAT?

47:25.970 --> 47:29.371
- ROGER.
- WHAT DID HE WANT?

47:29.480 --> 47:31.732
IT TURNS OUT SISSY
WAS THE BOARD CHAIR

47:31.840 --> 47:34.741
- OF AN ADOPTION AGENCY ONCE.
- YEAH...

47:34.850 --> 47:38.274
SHE CALLED IN A FAVOR,
AND SHE SAID WE COULD
ADOPT THROUGH THEM,

47:38.380 --> 47:41.747
- IF WE STILL WANTED TO.
- WE KIND OF MADE
A COMMITMENT TO MARY.

47:41.850 --> 47:45.581
I KNOW, BUT WE DON'T KNOW
FOR SURE THAT THAT'S REALLY
GOING TO WORK OUT.

47:45.690 --> 47:47.328
WE ALWAYS SAID
WE'D PURSUE BOTH OPTIONS

47:47.430 --> 47:49.853
UNTIL IT MADE SENSE
TO STOP, RIGHT?

47:49.960 --> 47:52.326
YEAH, I GUESS SO.

47:57.000 --> 47:59.639
SO NOW ROGER'S
YOUR HERO?

48:07.080 --> 48:09.913
SO YOU GOT LIKE ALMOST NO
HAIRCUT YESTERDAY, RIGHT?

48:10.020 --> 48:14.013
HE JUST TOOK A LITTLE
OFF THE TOP.

48:25.530 --> 48:28.590
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

48:32.270 --> 48:36.104
NOWHERE.
I STAYED AT MY HOUSE.

48:37.580 --> 48:40.401
YOU FUCKED SOMEBODY.

48:40.510 --> 48:43.570
IT'S OKAY.

48:43.680 --> 48:45.545
I'M NOT MAD.

48:45.650 --> 48:48.744
JUST TELL ME WHO IT WAS.

48:48.850 --> 48:51.182
WAS IT THAT DIVORCED GUY?

48:51.290 --> 48:54.919
- BILLY, COME ON.
- I FORGIVE YOU, CLAIRE.

48:55.030 --> 48:57.954
YOU CAN JUST ADMIT IT.

48:59.630 --> 49:03.691
JUST-- JUST BE
HONEST WITH ME.

49:06.140 --> 49:09.371
YEAH, IT WAS HIM.

49:12.250 --> 49:14.206
OKAY.

49:22.560 --> 49:24.414
WILL YOU FUCK ME NOW?

49:24.520 --> 49:25.953
- PLEASE.
- NO.

49:26.060 --> 49:28.620
- YOU KNOW I FORGIVE YOU,
CLAIRE, HMM?
- NO.

49:28.730 --> 49:31.392
IT'S OKAY.

49:31.500 --> 49:32.899
JUST FUCK ME NOW.

49:33.000 --> 49:36.128
- NO. NO!
- COME ON, TAKE OFF
YOUR PANTS.

49:36.240 --> 49:39.403
- PLEASE? COME ON.
- GET THE FUCK AWAY FROM ME!

49:39.510 --> 49:40.431
BUT I FORGIVE YOU.

49:40.540 --> 49:43.600
(crying )

49:43.710 --> 49:46.645
- COME ON, I NEED
TO BE INDE YOU.

49:55.990 --> 49:59.380
(crying )

50:11.470 --> 50:14.109
I'M SORRY.

